- row-bytes=0 -> read-only?  No: orthogonal.  read_only strided sources
  (read_only=1, row_bytes>0) and single-row writable outputs (read_only=0,
  row_bytes=0) are both legitimate.
- thread one umbra_buf[] through interp rather than three-pointer SoA we have now
- would interpreter / JIT be simpler if the inner core loop were 1D and driven
  from the outside with normal C in e.g. umbra_jit_run() to make it 2D?
